<content>
        
    
HOUSTON Aug 9 (Reuters) - BP Plc (BP.L) (BP.N) said on
Monday it has made an initial deposit of $3 billion into a $20
billion fund to pay for its Gulf of Mexico oil spill.

 Citigroup Inc (C.N) will serve as the corporate trustee and
paying agent for the account, BP said in a news release.
  (Reporting by Anna Driver in Houston)




